gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: National Transportation Atlas Database metadata states - The Amtrak Stations database is a geographic data set containing Amtrak intercity railroad passenger terminals. Attribute data include services and passenger amenities provided at the station. Data includes Amtrak railroad including some old stations that closed. Data currentness is reported at July 2000. Data does not include regional commuter railroad stations that also serve as Amtrak service, only stations in the Fixed-Guideway Transit Network. See Completeness report for more detail on station inclusion.

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: BROAD, GENERAL information for planning, development, and research in Indiana National Transportation Atlas Database metadata states - "The data set provides location and attribute information for use in national and regional cartographic and network analysis applications."

gmd:credit.gco:CharacterString: Indiana Statewide GIS database was produced under an Indiana Department of Transportation contract. Data is from the National Transportation Atlas Database (NTAD) produced by the Bureau of Transportation Statistics. gmd:measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: Bureau of Transportation Statistics metadata reports - "All point records are represented by a single coordinate pair and a unique feature identifier; the Amtrak Station Code (stored in the FEATURID field). Attribute data can be matched to specific point records using this identifier."

Bureau of Transportation Statistics metadata reports - "The database includes all Amtrak railroad and thruway bus stations listed in the Amtrak timetables mentioned above. Also included are 1)Amtrak railroad stations listed in earlier releases of this database that are now closed and 2) future Amtrak stations that can be identified from either their inclusion in the timetables or published intentions to increase Amtrak service. Regional commuter railroad stations that are not also served by Amtrak are not included in this version; those stations are currently included in the Fixed-Guideway Transit Network database. The database does not include information on passenger boarding's; those data are considered to be proprietary by Amtrak."

Bureau of Transportation Statistics metadata reports - "Attribute data were extracted from the station listings in the Spring/Summer 2000 Amtrak National and Summer/Fall 2000 Amtrak Northeast Timetables, and reflect station characteristics as of July 9, 2000. Additional data, as required, were obtained from earlier year timetables."

Bureau of Transportation Statistics metadata reports - "Stations having valid street addresses were geocoded to 1995 TIGER/Line(TM)street and railroad centerline files. Positional accuracy for those points is consistent with the accuracy of 1995 TIGER/Line(TM) files, or within about 50 meters of their true position. Stations with ambiguous or incomplete street addresses were positioned using a combination of street name, nearest railroad centerline, and place name. Positional accuracy for these points may vary from 100 to 1000 meters of their true location. The PA attribute indicates the estimated 'goodness' of the location."
Vertical accuracy was not a factor in the digital production of the data set. No quantitative tests were performed.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Bureau of Transportation Statistics metadata reports - "Each Amtrak railroad or thruway bus station identified in the Amtrak Timetables was initially geocoded based on its street address and ZIP Code, using the geocoding procedures in TransCAD (TM) software and the TIGER/Line(TM) 1995 street centerline databases. Stations with ambiguous street addresses were then located using a combination of geographic cues, including location of nearest railroad tracks, location of Standard Point Location Code (SPLC) place names, location of Census Named Places, and commercial road atlases. Stations with no street address and stations located in Canada were manually located based on place name and location of nearest railroad service." CREDIT "The Federal Railroad Administration compiled the data building on version 3 of these data compiled by Bruce D. Spear and published by the Bureau of Transportation Statistics."

Amtrak locations created in TransCAD were converted to ArcView shapefiles and made available for download from the website for the National Transportation Atlas (HTTP://www.bts.gov/gis/ntatlas/natlas.html). See Process Contact for details about this step.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Bernardin, Lochmueller and Associates downloaded the Amtrak stations shapefile from the National Transportation Atlas Database website (HTTP://www.bts.gov/gis/ntatlas/natlas.html) and selected out only those stations in the state of Indiana. File was transformed from geographic, to UTM Zone 16, NAD83, meters. Fields RR3-6 were deleted because no information existed in this subset.

This metadata was pre-parsed and parsed using CNS (Chew and Spit. v 2.6.1) and MP (Metadata Parser, v 2.7.1) software written by Peter N. Schweitzer (United States Geological Survey). The errors generated by MP were all addressed and corrected, except that no values were assigned to "Abscissa_Resolution" and "Ordinate_Resolution."

The following field were deleted from the dbf table using ESRI ArcView 3.2 because the fields provided little or no information: State, StFips, Version, Revision, Pa . The file was saved as a UTM 16, NAD83 projection.
